      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HAPPY ETHICS (1) was game in defeat when finished in the minors last start over the 520m at this track, running a slick 29.62 in a Grade 5. In the money latest and can measure up here. RITZA SOPHIE (7) was a last start winner (29.55) at this track in a NG and will jump from box 7 for the first time. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. One of the prime contenders. STOMP SHUFFLE (3) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 6 lengths at this track in a handy 29.79 beating Zipping Ruffian. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. KUNG FU ETHICS (2) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot as favourite most recently.",
